1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,003
[♪ upbeat music plays]

2
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

3
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,797
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

4
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,966
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:51,635
[♪ mischievous music plays]

6
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:58,934
You lying bastard!

7
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:00,602
[gasps]

8
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:06,275
What are you gonna do
about my precious money?

9
00:01:06,358 --> 00:01:08,527
What are you gonna do about my 15 million?

10
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,487
Oh, no. What do we do?

11
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:12,197
Oh, no.

12
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,366
Are you okay?

13
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:16,827
[gasps] Mr. Park! What are you doing?

14
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:20,872
The insurance company told me
that I have angina,

15
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:22,249
not myocardial infarction!

16
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,043
And they won't cover angina.

17
00:01:25,127 --> 00:01:29,464
- You did this just because of that?
- "Just because of that"? Wow.

18
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:31,925
So 15 million is a joke to you?

19
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:33,885
[sighs]

20
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:37,222
When angina progresses,
it becomes a myocardial infarction.

21
00:01:37,306 --> 00:01:38,432
Exactly!

22
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:40,475
So it wasn't a myocardial infarction!

23
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:44,313
You should've just given me
antacids like I said,

24
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:46,064
so I could've gone
to the hospital next morning!

25
00:01:46,148 --> 00:01:48,650
Why the hell did you cause
such a scene with the chopper?

26
00:01:48,734 --> 00:01:51,778
I'm out 15 million
and can't even get my insurance payout.

27
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:55,240
If I had prescribed you antacids
and let you wait to go to the hospital,

28
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,617
you would've gotten it.

29
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,705
As a life insurance payout.

30
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,749
- What are you saying?
- What?

31
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,083
[Hari] No…

32
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:06,710
Life insurance?

33
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:09,755
You goddamn quack!

34
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:12,299
Mr. Park! Let's talk it out!

35
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,343
- Let go!
- Let go of…

36
00:02:15,677 --> 00:02:16,970
- You…
- [Hari] Mr. Park.

37
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:19,598
There seems to be a misunderstanding.

38
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,725
We'll check on the situation first

39
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,226
- and…
- [Jiui screams]

40
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,520
We're really sorry! Just a second!

41
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:27,939
[Mr. Park] Hey!

42
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,233
Where do you think you're going?

43
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:32,277
You lying quack!

44
00:02:32,361 --> 00:02:34,488
Give me back my 15 million!

45
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,906
[pants]

46
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:44,831
[sighs]

47
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:55,550
[screams]

48
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:58,595
[spits]

49
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:02,891
EPISODE 3
GETTING THROUGH ANOTHER DAY

50
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:05,977
[Ms. Hwang] <i>Oh, my. This is bad.</i>

51
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:09,189
Mr. Park's normally such a gentleman,

52
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:13,318
but once you get into a fight with him,
he never lets it go.

53
00:03:13,402 --> 00:03:16,071
He's like a bulldog gnawing on a bone.

54
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:17,155
[growls]

55
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:18,573
[Ms. Hwang chuckles]

56
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:20,158
[clears throat]

57
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:23,078
Anyway, you're really in for it, Dr. Do.

58
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:24,538
CLIFFSIDE RAW FISH RESTAURANT

59
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:25,622
- Auntie.
- We're here.

60
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:26,957
Goodness.

61
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,501
I'm sorry to tell you this…

62
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:30,961
- What is it?
- [clears throat]

63
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,922
We're all out of ingredients.

64
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:35,298
- You're…
- What?

65
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:37,426
You're all out of ingredients?

66
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:42,055
You told us to come over
for pork cutlets just 20 minutes ago.

67
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:43,390
Exactly.

68
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:47,310
I swear everything was fine
20 minutes ago, but…

69
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:49,438
- [sighs]
- [clears throat]

70
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,524
- Hello, Mr. Park.
- Hello.

71
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:54,359
[Mr. Park sighs]

72
00:03:54,443 --> 00:03:57,154
That's just how the world works.

73
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:58,655
Isn't it?

74
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,076
[sighs]

75
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:07,831
Just a week ago, I myself would have
never guessed that I'd be down 15 million.

76
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:09,458
You know?

77
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,006
I think it's because of me,
so I'll eat on my own.

78
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,090
We're good now, right?

79
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,968
- Enjoy your meals.
- [Hari] I'll go with him.

80
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,387
I'll see you later. [chuckles]

81
00:04:22,471 --> 00:04:23,722
[Ms. Hwang] Oh, dear.

82
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:29,060
GENERAL GOODS FOR SALE

83
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:32,147
[Hari] Gosh.

84
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:39,029
Why did you come with me?

85
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,114
What if Mr. Park starts gunning for you?

86
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:44,242
Maybe I'll be the one gunning for him.

87
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:47,871
[chuckles] Don't worry.

88
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:52,334
[sighs]

89
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,379
Do you regret it?

90
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:00,967
Do you wish you'd just
pretended not to notice and let him go?

91
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:02,969
[clicks tongue]

92
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:07,098
Whether I regret it or not is irrelevant.

93
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:10,769
Because like him or not,
lacerations are lacerations?

94
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:13,855
[sighs]

95
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,858
I'm sure Mr. Park
just lost his temper momentarily

96
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:19,152
because of the sudden massive bill.

97
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:21,488
I'm sure he'll let up soon.

98
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,949
What more could he possibly do?

99
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:25,158
Hmm? [chuckles]

100
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:32,332
[yelps]

101
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:35,752
[Jiui] <i>Turns out</i>

102
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:37,963
<i>there was more he could do.</i>

103
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,297
Goodness me.

104
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:42,551
Thank you all
for your hard work in the rain.

105
00:05:42,634 --> 00:05:43,635
You're here?

106
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:45,220
Please don't mention it.

107
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:49,808
This is the kind of work
we should be doing for our residents.

108
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,893
[Mr. Park chuckles] Well, lookee here.

109
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,020
Dr. Do Jiui.

110
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:56,898
You're a proper garbage man.

111
00:05:56,982 --> 00:06:01,069
Sure would've been nice
if you had just done that from the start.

112
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:02,863
That way I'd still have 15 million.

113
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:04,114
- [staff chuckle]
- [groans]

114
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,657
[Ms. Hwang] Right.

115
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,409
[♪ tense music plays]

116
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:09,578
I can't take this anymore.

117
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:11,621
[groans]

118
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:13,790
- [groans]
- Are you okay?

119
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:15,250
What was that for?

120
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:18,169
- I thought a fight was going to--
- [Mr. Park] What?

121
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:19,713
Do you have something to say?

122
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,923
It's nothing. You take care now.

123
00:06:22,007 --> 00:06:23,466
Of course, he has nothing to say.

124
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,135
Nothing to say, right?

125
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:28,680
Just try to bear with it.

126
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,640
I'm sure he's just frustrated.

127
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:33,768
Why do you keep telling me
to bear with it?

128
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,521
What did I do wrong just now?

129
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:40,817
This is the least we could do for them.
They're the residents, after all.

130
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,193
No.

131
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,404
I won't stand for this anymore.

132
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:45,864
I have no reason to!

133
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:48,909
[sighs]

134
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:50,910
[stammers, sighs]

135
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:53,872
[sighs]

136
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:58,418
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

137
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:01,504
[coughing]

138
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:08,553
Goodness. Look how inconvenient
things are for the both of us,

139
00:07:08,637 --> 00:07:11,806
because you'll only prescribe me
three days' worth of medicine.

140
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:13,433
Your cough isn't getting better.

141
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:15,977
Maybe because the doctor
is bad at his job.

142
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:22,150
Do you take any other medication
or have you fallen ill before?

143
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,401
Let's see…

144
00:07:23,485 --> 00:07:24,486
No.

145
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,450
Let me take a look in your mouth.
Would you say "Ah" for me?

146
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:36,081
I'll also take your temperature.

147
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,249
For the love of…

148
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:40,710
What's with all the prodding and poking?

149
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:43,296
Chronic coughs are a bad sign.

150
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,299
It might be good
to go to the mainland and get an X-ray--

151
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:49,594
Why are you so eager
to send patients off to the mainland?

152
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,347
I'm not a sucker like the chief!

153
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:55,809
I couldn't afford that
in my wildest dreams,

154
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,268
so just give me my meds now!

155
00:07:57,352 --> 00:08:00,480
I'm not a vending machine
that just dispenses your medicine!

156
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,399
What?

157
00:08:03,358 --> 00:08:04,401
Go wait outside.

158
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:07,070
Okay.

159
00:08:11,783 --> 00:08:12,867
Allow me to explain--

160
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:19,332
Hello, ma'am. What brings you in today?

161
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:22,627
It's the same problem as always. My knees.

162
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:24,129
Your knees?

163
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:27,090
That's why I've captured these
and brought them with me.

164
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,760
I heard these are amazing
for aching knees.

165
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,846
Oh, ma'am!

166
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,973
What are…

167
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:36,349
- What are those?
- [chuckles]

168
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,351
What do you think?

169
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:42,063
I brought them for bee sting therapy.
You know how to administer it, right?

170
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:43,231
[chuckles]

171
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:44,441
Gosh, ma'am.

172
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:48,319
You're not meant to administer
bee sting therapy using actual bees.

173
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:51,489
You're supposed to refine the venom
extracted from a honeybee

174
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:53,408
and inject it using a needle.

175
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,577
So please put that away.

176
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,830
Well, damn.
That was a total waste of time and effort.

177
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:01,332
[groans]

178
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:04,294
Ma'am, you'll have to take this with you.

179
00:09:05,003 --> 00:09:08,006
What use would I have for that?
It's not like I can eat it.

180
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,175
[sighs] But I can't eat it either…

181
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:13,136
- Ms. Eom?
- Yes?

182
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,847
Go take a seat and wait, please.

183
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:19,476
What is it?

184
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,437
[chuckles]

185
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,397
Would you mind putting this away for me?

186
00:09:24,481 --> 00:09:26,483
You want me to put it away?

187
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:27,692
Why's that?

188
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:31,154
You think a country bumpkin like me
can handle bees with my bare hands?

189
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:35,075
N-Not exactly.

190
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:37,702
[sighs]

191
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:42,248
Fine. Your wish is my command,
your highness.

192
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,168
- Ooh…
- [gasps]

193
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,628
Cut it out.

194
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:51,341
- [exclaims]
- Seriously! I told you to cut it out!

195
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,718
Just get out! What's wrong with you?

196
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:54,886
- [exclaims]
- [screams]

197
00:09:54,969 --> 00:09:57,514
Come on! [breathes shakily]

198
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,643
- [screams]
- [gasps]

199
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:03,770
It stings!

200
00:10:14,197 --> 00:10:17,909
[exclaiming, screaming]

201
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,662
It stings!

202
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,131
I'm sorry, Ms. Eom.

203
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:37,053
[sighs] What's going on?

204
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:39,139
- [Ms. Hwang] Run!
- [Jucheon] Oh, you see…

205
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,766
What is it?

206
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:44,644
[Jucheon stammers, yelps]

207
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,355
[screaming]

208
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:49,941
Run for your lives, everyone!

209
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:53,278
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

210
00:10:57,699 --> 00:10:59,367
- That stings! Get out!
- The door!

211
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:01,619
Run!

212
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:08,042
- Stay away!
- Hurry!

213
00:11:08,126 --> 00:11:10,378
- Hurry!
- Stay still!

214
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:11,462
- Here!
- Stay still!

215
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,548
Stay still!

216
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:15,049
[groans] That stings!

217
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:17,177
Why are there bees in the center?

218
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:19,470
- How on earth did this happen?
- Well…

219
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:23,183
Hold on a minute.

220
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,602
- What about Dr. Chiyeon?
- What?

221
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,937
- Dr. Chiyeon.
- Huh?

222
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:29,480
Huh?

223
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:32,567
[panting]

224
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,862
EXAM ROOM 2

225
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:38,948
[♪ heroic music plays]

226
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:57,926
[exclaims]

227
00:11:58,885 --> 00:12:00,511
That stings. Come on.

228
00:12:00,595 --> 00:12:01,930
Stay still.

229
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:03,264
Seriously.

230
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:07,018
Are you kidding me?
Look what they've done to my cute face.

231
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,187
This is ridiculous.

232
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,147
We got bees unleashed on us,

233
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:14,150
but Ms. Sinhye's telling us
to just stay put.

234
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:15,360
Of course, we should.

235
00:12:15,944 --> 00:12:17,487
We're civil servants.

236
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:19,489
"Civil servants"?

237
00:12:20,198 --> 00:12:22,951
Well, if we're civil servants,

238
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:25,495
they should at least
cover our expenses properly.

239
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:29,123
I've been buying my needles
for the past few months.

240
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:30,667
Self-funded needles!

241
00:12:31,501 --> 00:12:35,505
I know they don't cost that much,
but it really grinds my gears.

242
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,882
- You shouldn't let that bother you.
- Why not?

243
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,717
Because we're doctors.

244
00:12:40,802 --> 00:12:43,263
We shouldn't let money
get in the way of saving lives,

245
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:44,347
as doctors.

246
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,891
But still, this is a bit…

247
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:48,101
[Hyeon] It's unfair.

248
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:50,770
But we're supposed to suck it up

249
00:12:51,813 --> 00:12:52,897
as soldiers.

250
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:56,234
- You said we were civil servants.
- We are civil servants.

251
00:12:56,818 --> 00:12:58,236
We're also soldiers

252
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:00,488
and doctors.

253
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:01,823
Hmm…

254
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:04,284
Sounds like a fancy way of saying
we're punching bags

255
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,202
that the whole town can use.

256
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:11,582
That's why you shouldn't try too hard.

257
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:15,295
Nothing will come of it.

258
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:27,974
[door opens, closes]

259
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:32,687
Did something happen to him
before he came to Pyeondongdo?

260
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:34,355
Uh…

261
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:40,194
I heard he was sued by a resident
he treated before he came here.

262
00:13:40,278 --> 00:13:41,487
[♪ sentimental music plays]

263
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:42,572
Someone sued him?

264
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:45,575
Two patients with puffer fish poisoning
were brought in,

265
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:51,039
but while he was treating one,
the other one apparently died of shock.

266
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:56,294
And the family of the deceased
sued Dr. Hyeon.

267
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:57,420
What? Are you…

268
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:00,298
That's ridiculous.

269
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,051
What's even more ridiculous

270
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:06,596
is that the person who survived
also sued him.

271
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:08,514
Why?

272
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:10,725
I guess they chose
to side with their own people

273
00:14:10,808 --> 00:14:12,894
rather than the doctor
who saved their life.

274
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,148
- [sighs]
- Even the person he trusted

275
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:20,359
to be on his side
told Dr. Hyeon not to fight it.

276
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:29,952
This is the least we could do for them.
They're the residents, after all.

277
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,456
Is Ms. Hari also on the residents' side?

278
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:37,126
EXAM ROOM

279
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,462
Hello, sir. What brings you here--

280
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:41,380
[resident] Prescribe this for me.

281
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:44,717
- What?
- I don't have time.

282
00:14:44,801 --> 00:14:46,803
So just prescribe it for me now.

283
00:14:50,056 --> 00:14:51,599
GOPU SYRUP, PSEUDOPHEDINE…

284
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:57,438
[Hyeon]
<i>That's why you shouldn't try too hard.</i>

285
00:14:57,522 --> 00:14:59,440
Nothing will come of it.

286
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:04,946
I'll write you a script.

287
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:07,073
GOPU SYRUP, PSEUDOPHEDINE

288
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,992
[resident] Then, since you're
writing me a script anyway--

289
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:12,578
I'll give you a lot.
Will 30 days' worth be enough?

290
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:15,623
Hot damn. That sounds great.

291
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:17,583
30-DAY PRESCRIPTION

292
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:19,710
Please wait outside.

293
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:20,878
Okay.

294
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:25,883
Wasn't expecting that.

295
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:33,099
[breathes heavily]

296
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,561
[Jiui] <i>True to the name, Pyeondongdo,</i>

297
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:40,314
<i>where only one thing matters to them</i>
<i>and that is comfort,</i>

298
00:15:40,398 --> 00:15:43,025
<i>I decided to find comfort for myself.</i>

299
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:48,489
My insides are in a knot,
and I keep gagging.

300
00:15:48,573 --> 00:15:50,867
So I'm here to pick up
some digestive medicine.

301
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,910
I'll write you your usual prescription.

302
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:54,912
30-DAY PRESCRIPTION

303
00:15:57,999 --> 00:16:02,545
I need some pain relief patches
and some meds for my arthritis.

304
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,714
Sure. Pick them up on your way out.

305
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:12,847
I've got canker sores…

306
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,932
I'll prescribe some Oremedy for you.

307
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:19,228
Well, I don't care about the ointment.

308
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:23,649
I was just wondering why I keep getting
so many canker sores…

309
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:27,153
Think it's 'cause my immunity's shot?

310
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:29,655
Do you think exercise
might make them heal?

311
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:31,365
Exercise for immunity?

312
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:33,451
Sure. It's great.

313
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:34,660
You should exercise.

314
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:37,330
I'm here to get some painkillers.

315
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:40,041
Would you like Talenol or Iburonfen?

316
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,877
Just give me whatever.

317
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:44,837
I'll give you both.

318
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,548
Oh… Okay.

319
00:16:48,049 --> 00:16:51,552
[coughing]

320
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:00,686
I'll prescribe you 30 days' worth.

321
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:04,607
DAYS: 30

322
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,611
[sighs]

323
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:11,489
[Ms. Hwang] You're right.

324
00:17:11,572 --> 00:17:12,949
They're both handsome.

325
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,283
- Yes.
- [Jangsu] Yes.

326
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:20,623
Here's thirty days' worth of medicine.

327
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:23,459
Take them in the morning and evening,
30 minutes after a meal.

328
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:27,630
Well, damn. That's more like it.

329
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:31,717
So 3 times 1 is 3,
which makes it 11,000 won.

330
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:34,053
- [chuckles] Right.
- [chuckles] Right.

331
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:36,639
Only take them twice a day
in the morning and evening!

332
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,182
- [Jangsu] Got it.
- Okay.

333
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:40,601
- Take care!
- See you next time.

334
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:49,193
[sighs]

335
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:52,363
[Hari clears throat]

336
00:17:54,532 --> 00:17:56,075
Dr. Do. [chuckles]

337
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,159
Yes?

338
00:17:57,827 --> 00:18:00,580
What's gotten into you recently?

339
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:03,666
What do you mean?

340
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:06,043
You prescribe whatever they ask for,

341
00:18:06,127 --> 00:18:08,296
and you send them away so quickly.

342
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:11,507
And prescribing a month's worth
of cough medicine like that--

343
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:14,051
You told me to let them have their way.

344
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:17,179
- What?
- I was doing what you told me to do.

345
00:18:18,306 --> 00:18:22,518
I know now that getting into fights
will do me no good whatsoever.

346
00:18:23,728 --> 00:18:26,147
[stammers] That's not what I--

347
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:30,192
I just need to stick it out for a year,
then leave, safe and sound.

348
00:18:30,276 --> 00:18:31,736
[scoffs]

349
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:35,364
Whatever happened to "Like them or not,
lacerations are lacerations?"

350
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:38,075
I guess I adjusted to life here.

351
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,121
I see.

352
00:18:42,705 --> 00:18:45,333
I get what kind of person you are now.

353
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:47,835
What?

354
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:50,963
I almost mistook you for a good doctor.

355
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,175
I'm just a civil servant.

356
00:18:55,051 --> 00:18:57,887
Actually, I'm not even a civil servant.
What even am I?

357
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:58,971
I'm nothing.

358
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:00,973
That's why no one will protect me!

359
00:19:01,057 --> 00:19:03,100
I'm not done talking! Where are you going?

360
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:07,521
Dr. Do.

361
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:10,775
You'll have to make rounds
on Madeokdo tomorrow.

362
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,487
- M-Madeokdo?
- Yes.

363
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:17,281
Don't worry, though.
Ms. Yuk will be accompanying you.

364
00:19:17,365 --> 00:19:18,824
[Hari] Ms. Hwang!

365
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:22,745
Can I go to Madeokdo
with Dr. Hyeon instead?

366
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:25,706
Me?

367
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:29,168
Well, this would be
our first Madeokdo visit,

368
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:31,379
so I figured it'd be awkward
for the patients

369
00:19:31,462 --> 00:19:33,631
if they're unacquainted
with both Dr. Do and me.

370
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:36,092
Wouldn't Dr. Hyeon be better
since he's been there?

371
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,677
Oh…

372
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:39,845
But Dr. Hyeon said he doesn't want--

373
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:41,097
[Hyeon] I'll go.

374
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:43,516
You're going to go on visits?

375
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:44,975
Let's leave early tomorrow.

376
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:46,519
Sure. [chuckles]

377
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:51,774
I guess that settles that.

378
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:53,484
[Ms. Hwang exclaims]

379
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:55,444
You must be so happy, Dr. Do!

380
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,530
- [Ms. Hwang chuckles]
- [Jiui sighs]

381
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:01,200
What does she want from me?

382
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:05,162
[sighs]

383
00:20:09,542 --> 00:20:11,419
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER
CLOSED

384
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:20,511
START

385
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:21,595
RECORD, STOP

386
00:20:23,806 --> 00:20:24,890
[sighs]

387
00:20:24,974 --> 00:20:27,977
[♪ serene music plays]

388
00:20:59,842 --> 00:21:02,720
[pants]

389
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:13,439
What the…

390
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:17,526
It's not like I said anything wrong.
Why do I have to bear with everything?

391
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:18,652
[scoffs]

392
00:21:19,153 --> 00:21:22,364
[phone buzzing]

393
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:24,992
Hello?

394
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,077
Dr. Jiui, where are you?

395
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:29,663
The supplies we ordered are here.

396
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:31,415
Could you pick them up for us?

397
00:21:31,499 --> 00:21:32,500
Thanks.

398
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,752
- [line disconnects]
- Hey…

399
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:39,131
I can't even…

400
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,467
Only take what's yours!

401
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,053
- Okay?
- Okay.

402
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:46,347
You don't wanna take someone else's stuff.

403
00:21:46,889 --> 00:21:48,432
- This one's mine.
- Yeah.

404
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:54,438
Looking for your delivery?

405
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,315
Yes.

406
00:21:56,941 --> 00:21:58,400
[Mr. Park] Look hard.

407
00:21:59,193 --> 00:22:04,573
I've had hand tremors
ever since I lost 15 million.

408
00:22:04,657 --> 00:22:06,784
I might have dropped it somewhere.

409
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:08,953
Those were supplies for the health center!

410
00:22:09,036 --> 00:22:10,996
That's none of my concern,

411
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,666
just as my 15 million
was none of your concern.

412
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,378
- [scoffs]
- [groans]

413
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:19,463
Oh!

414
00:22:19,547 --> 00:22:20,798
There it is.

415
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:22,716
The delivery for the Public Health Center.

416
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:35,896
On your way back,
drop off those remaining deliveries. Okay?

417
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:37,982
What?

418
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:39,984
They're all for old folks here.

419
00:22:40,734 --> 00:22:44,655
Isn't it a PH doc's duty to do everything
for the health of the residents?

420
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:47,825
Isn't it?

421
00:22:47,908 --> 00:22:50,327
PYEONDONGDO VILLAGE HALL

422
00:22:50,411 --> 00:22:51,787
Use this if you want to.

423
00:22:53,122 --> 00:22:54,456
[scoffs]

424
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:57,710
Are you sure that's yours?

425
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:08,470
What are you doing?

426
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:10,264
Ah…

427
00:23:10,347 --> 00:23:12,933
I'm putting on sunscreen.
I don't want to get burned.

428
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:14,768
The sun's not even up yet though.

429
00:23:14,852 --> 00:23:17,187
Sunscreen's super important, you know.

430
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,398
Oh…

431
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:20,858
Do you want some?

432
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:23,944
[♪ comedic music plays]

433
00:23:25,446 --> 00:23:26,447
What is it?

434
00:23:27,781 --> 00:23:29,033
It's nothing.

435
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,619
Come on. Put some on, okay?

436
00:23:31,702 --> 00:23:34,705
You're meant to apply it all the time.

437
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:37,958
Early in the morning, late at night,
before bed and even during winter.

438
00:23:38,042 --> 00:23:39,585
No, really. I'm good.

439
00:23:39,668 --> 00:23:41,545
Don't play coy with me.

440
00:23:41,629 --> 00:23:43,589
Men wear it too nowadays.

441
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:44,882
Give me your hand.

442
00:23:44,965 --> 00:23:46,050
Smear it all over.

443
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:49,053
Don't miss any spots.

444
00:23:53,641 --> 00:23:56,226
No… Wait!

445
00:24:01,649 --> 00:24:03,067
[sighs] Damn it.

446
00:24:09,114 --> 00:24:11,533
[groans] Seriously…

447
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:25,798
HANDLE WITH CARE

448
00:24:25,881 --> 00:24:26,882
"Handle with care."

449
00:24:28,342 --> 00:24:29,802
"Handle with care."

450
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:35,474
Yuk Ha…

451
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:36,684
RECIPIENT: YUK HARI

452
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:38,227
Ms. Yuk Hari.

453
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,436
HANDLE WITH CARE

454
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:40,729
"Handle with care"?

455
00:24:41,897 --> 00:24:46,402
In the spirit of handling it with care,
I should probably let her know.

456
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,404
Yes, definitely.

457
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:50,322
Let's see…

458
00:24:56,203 --> 00:24:59,873
<i>Ms. Yuk, I came across your delivery</i>
<i>and it seemed important, so…</i>

459
00:25:03,377 --> 00:25:05,713
What the…

460
00:25:06,547 --> 00:25:08,173
[groans] No!

461
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:10,217
Delete.

462
00:25:10,968 --> 00:25:13,012
Come on. Delete.

463
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:14,596
THIS MESSAGE HAS BEEN DELETED
FOR YOU ONLY

464
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,098
<i>No! Wait!</i>

465
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:20,894
[gasps, exclaims]

466
00:25:23,105 --> 00:25:25,357
What… What am I going to do?

467
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:28,318
[exclaims] Come on!

468
00:25:28,402 --> 00:25:31,530
PYEONDONGDO, MADEOKDO, GAYEONGDO

469
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:32,614
[phone chimes]

470
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:35,826
[gasps] What the heck?

471
00:25:36,744 --> 00:25:38,287
- What is this?
- What's wrong?

472
00:25:39,163 --> 00:25:40,414
What?

473
00:25:40,497 --> 00:25:41,749
Uh…

474
00:25:41,832 --> 00:25:43,292
It's nothing.

475
00:25:47,755 --> 00:25:48,756
Oh, my.

476
00:25:48,839 --> 00:25:50,340
Thank you for coming.

477
00:25:50,424 --> 00:25:51,592
I'm the village chief.

478
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:53,594
[chuckles]

479
00:25:53,677 --> 00:25:54,970
Goodness me.

480
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:56,555
I guess you had a pretty rough trip.

481
00:25:57,139 --> 00:25:58,390
You're as pale as a ghost.

482
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:01,852
- Excuse me?
- It's nothing. Come this way.

483
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,238
[Ms. Hwang] You brought the packages?

484
00:26:13,322 --> 00:26:15,407
- Yes.
- [Ms. Hwang] Well done.

485
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:17,159
Now organize everything in there.

486
00:26:18,035 --> 00:26:19,620
Organize everything too?

487
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:30,589
RECIPIENT: YUK HARI

488
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:38,472
What brings you here today?

489
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:43,852
Doctor, my boy, Juman,
normally eats like he's got a hollow leg,

490
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:46,814
but today he hasn't touched
his food all day.

491
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:48,857
Not even a drop of water.

492
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:51,693
He has a hollow leg?

493
00:26:53,028 --> 00:26:56,865
He normally has a large appetite
but didn't even have a sip of water today.

494
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:57,950
Ah…

495
00:26:58,575 --> 00:27:00,160
I'll need to examine the patient.

496
00:27:00,244 --> 00:27:02,746
Is he not able to come here?

497
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:03,872
Oh, my.

498
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:05,499
He's here with me.

499
00:27:05,582 --> 00:27:07,459
Goodness, Juman. Get out here.

500
00:27:07,543 --> 00:27:08,877
- Goodness me.
- [Juman whimpers]

501
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:12,506
Please hurry and take a look at him.

502
00:27:12,589 --> 00:27:15,134
I'm worried my son might be sick!

503
00:27:17,177 --> 00:27:20,556
[Juman whimpers]

504
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:22,683
Goodness.

505
00:27:22,766 --> 00:27:24,184
You haven't treated him yet.

506
00:27:24,268 --> 00:27:26,270
Where are you going?

507
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:31,275
MADEOKDO SENIOR CENTER

508
00:27:31,358 --> 00:27:33,777
That old woman, she's not exactly normal.

509
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:36,280
She's not all there.

510
00:27:36,363 --> 00:27:39,449
She thinks that dog is her son
who died when he was little.

511
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:42,077
- Ah…
- [sighs]

512
00:27:43,245 --> 00:27:44,246
[village chief] Gosh.

513
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:47,666
[Hari] But… [sighs]

514
00:27:49,334 --> 00:27:51,461
- Oh, man.
- [sighs]

515
00:27:57,301 --> 00:27:58,468
[line connects]

516
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:02,180
[Hyeon] Bro, can you talk right now?

517
00:28:03,891 --> 00:28:06,768
Well, she's saying that her dog
won't eat or drink any water.

518
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:08,395
What am I supposed to do?

519
00:28:10,606 --> 00:28:11,732
The weight?

520
00:28:12,774 --> 00:28:14,276
Around three kilos, I think?

521
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:18,697
Okay, I'll get back to you later.

522
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,658
- Yeah.
- [line disconnects]

523
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:24,536
[inhales sharply] Juman…

524
00:28:31,668 --> 00:28:33,045
How's Juman doing?

525
00:28:34,755 --> 00:28:37,049
It's not serious, is it?

526
00:28:37,132 --> 00:28:40,135
If Juman ends up passing away,
I'll follow him.

527
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:49,061
I think we should monitor him
for a couple days.

528
00:28:49,978 --> 00:28:53,690
Could be he's being fussy with food,
so try giving him treats he likes.

529
00:28:53,774 --> 00:28:56,902
If he eats his treats,
he's probably not sick.

530
00:28:57,778 --> 00:29:00,530
Goodness, I don't know how to thank you.

531
00:29:00,614 --> 00:29:04,034
Juman, thank the good doctor, okay?

532
00:29:04,826 --> 00:29:06,411
Okay. Goodbye, Juman.

533
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:07,663
- [barks, growls]
- [Hyeon groans]

534
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:09,164
Are you okay?

535
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:10,290
Oh, goodness me.

536
00:29:10,374 --> 00:29:11,708
[groans, sighs]

537
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:17,923
[sighs]

538
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:20,175
I was peeling onions for the dinner shift,

539
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:22,636
but I ended up peeling my fingers as well.

540
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:24,763
[Geumja groans]

541
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:30,435
It's a big wound and it's deep,
so I think you'll need stitches.

542
00:29:30,519 --> 00:29:32,980
You should go to the mainland
to get it treated.

543
00:29:33,063 --> 00:29:34,272
The mainland?

544
00:29:34,815 --> 00:29:36,483
What am I going to do?

545
00:29:36,566 --> 00:29:38,777
We even have a group reservation today.

546
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:41,947
[sighs] Can't I get it treated here?

547
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:44,324
[Jiui] <i>It's a big wound and it's deep.</i>

548
00:29:46,076 --> 00:29:48,286
<i>If she were to file a complaint</i>
<i>about it leaving a scar…</i>

549
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:50,455
It's because there might be nerve damage.

550
00:29:51,957 --> 00:29:54,084
You'll want to get a proper checkup.

551
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:56,920
[sighs]

552
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:58,672
[Hyeon groans]

553
00:30:02,676 --> 00:30:04,261
I guess you like dogs, huh?

554
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:06,805
No.

555
00:30:08,181 --> 00:30:10,267
I'm scared of them
because I got bitten once.

556
00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:11,893
Really?

557
00:30:13,061 --> 00:30:14,062
Then why…

558
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:17,566
Because it seemed to bother you.

559
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:21,820
Was that not the case?

560
00:30:24,239 --> 00:30:25,240
[chuckles]

561
00:30:26,283 --> 00:30:27,284
It's just…

562
00:30:28,827 --> 00:30:30,829
She reminded me of my grandma,

563
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:36,626
and I felt bad for her since the dog
was her only source of warmth.

564
00:30:37,419 --> 00:30:38,587
That's it.

565
00:30:44,384 --> 00:30:46,928
I'm sorry you have to leave
before even grabbing a meal.

566
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:48,346
You even got bitten by a dog.

567
00:30:48,430 --> 00:30:49,556
Uh… [chuckles]

568
00:30:49,639 --> 00:30:50,807
It's fine.

569
00:30:50,891 --> 00:30:52,893
How about you treat us
to a lot of good food

570
00:30:52,976 --> 00:30:54,436
- on our next visit?
- Okay.

571
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:56,605
[elderly resident] Doctor!

572
00:30:56,688 --> 00:30:58,148
Doctor!

573
00:30:58,231 --> 00:30:59,858
Doctor!

574
00:30:59,941 --> 00:31:02,277
Oh, no.

575
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,695
This is bad.

576
00:31:03,779 --> 00:31:06,281
My boy, Juman…

577
00:31:06,364 --> 00:31:08,533
Enough! They have to get on their boat!

578
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:11,203
Oh, gosh! He's bleeding!

579
00:31:11,286 --> 00:31:13,497
He's going to die!

580
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:15,415
- Look…
- Okay, I'll take a look.

581
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:19,878
Hey,

582
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:22,255
stay still.

583
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:24,132
Let me take a look at you.

584
00:31:25,634 --> 00:31:28,178
- [growls]
- What is it?

585
00:31:29,346 --> 00:31:30,889
There's a splinter stuck in him.

586
00:31:31,515 --> 00:31:33,558
We should remove it and stop the bleeding.

587
00:31:36,228 --> 00:31:37,395
But…

588
00:31:38,688 --> 00:31:39,689
But?

589
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:43,360
I'm not sure I can do it.

590
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:47,280
[growls, barks]

591
00:31:49,616 --> 00:31:52,035
[♪ tense music plays]

592
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:53,328
We don't have time.

593
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:56,665
Just thirty seconds. No more.
Are you sure you can do this?

594
00:31:58,291 --> 00:31:59,668
Let's do this in one go.

595
00:32:01,545 --> 00:32:02,587
One.

596
00:32:03,463 --> 00:32:04,756
Two.

597
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:06,633
Three. Now!

598
00:32:21,606 --> 00:32:22,774
[groans]

599
00:32:22,858 --> 00:32:24,860
[♪ comical music plays]

600
00:32:37,164 --> 00:32:39,374
- Done. We did it!
- It's done? We did it?

601
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:42,252
- I got it out! We did it!
- We did it! [exclaims]

602
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:44,671
How's my Juman doing?

603
00:32:44,754 --> 00:32:46,047
We got it out!

604
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:49,926
- [chuckles] Look!
- [elderly resident] Oh, thank you so much!

605
00:32:50,010 --> 00:32:51,970
- Thank you.
- You got it out. Wow.

606
00:32:52,053 --> 00:32:54,222
- [elderly resident sobs]
- [Hyeon sighs]

607
00:32:55,765 --> 00:32:57,976
Thank you.

608
00:32:59,603 --> 00:33:00,937
[groans]

609
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:03,648
[watch beeps]

610
00:33:07,694 --> 00:33:11,489
Hey, when will they be returning anyway?

611
00:33:11,573 --> 00:33:12,908
[Ms. Hwang] Gosh, I know.

612
00:33:13,617 --> 00:33:16,912
The last boat was a while ago,
so I wonder if they got on.

613
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:19,414
- Goodness.
- [phone ringing]

614
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:20,957
Oh… [grunts]

615
00:33:26,213 --> 00:33:27,964
Yes, Public Health Center.

616
00:33:28,048 --> 00:33:31,927
- [Hari] <i>Ms. Hwang…</i>
- Hey, is something wrong?

617
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:34,262
We had to treat
an urgent last-minute patient

618
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:36,139
and missed the last boat.

619
00:33:36,223 --> 00:33:38,350
[Ms. Hwang] <i>An urgent last-minute patient?</i>

620
00:33:38,433 --> 00:33:41,561
Don't worry. We treated him well.

621
00:33:41,645 --> 00:33:44,648
Then do you have a place to stay?

622
00:33:44,731 --> 00:33:47,692
Yes. One of the residents here
offered a place.

623
00:33:47,776 --> 00:33:50,570
[Ms. Hwang sighs] That's a relief.

624
00:33:50,654 --> 00:33:52,948
In that case, good luck with that.

625
00:33:53,531 --> 00:33:54,532
Mmm…

626
00:33:55,617 --> 00:33:56,701
What is it?

627
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:58,954
Something urgent came up,

628
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:01,831
so Ms. Hari and Dr. Chiyeon
missed the last boat.

629
00:34:01,915 --> 00:34:03,833
They'll be back tomorrow.

630
00:34:03,917 --> 00:34:05,085
T-Tomorrow?

631
00:34:05,168 --> 00:34:06,378
Yes.

632
00:34:06,461 --> 00:34:08,213
Wow. No way.

633
00:34:08,922 --> 00:34:11,508
So these things really do
happen in real life, huh?

634
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:13,802
What do you mean by that?

635
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:17,931
It's like something out of
a late '80s movie.

636
00:34:18,515 --> 00:34:20,892
- A movie?
- There he goes again, talking nonsense.

637
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:22,727
[Jucheon] Get this.

638
00:34:22,811 --> 00:34:26,940
A young man and woman go to an island,
and they miss the last boat.

639
00:34:27,649 --> 00:34:29,401
And you know what happens next?

640
00:34:29,484 --> 00:34:31,736
There's only one room available.

641
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:33,822
Only one room…

642
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:36,616
available?

643
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,702
[♪ dramatic music playing]

644
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:49,129
[innkeeper] What to do?

645
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:51,548
There's only one room left.

646
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:52,757
Oh, my!

647
00:34:52,841 --> 00:34:55,302
[Jucheon] <i>The sky's grown dark</i>
<i>in an unfamiliar town.</i>

648
00:34:55,385 --> 00:34:58,471
They're saying they only have one room.

649
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:03,184
Well, I suppose it cannot be helped.

650
00:35:03,268 --> 00:35:06,229
[Jucheon] <i>They only have</i>
<i>each other to rely on…</i>

651
00:35:06,313 --> 00:35:07,355
[Hari sighs]

652
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:09,566
Mmm.

653
00:35:10,525 --> 00:35:12,611
- [Hari sighs, gasps]
- Ms. Yuk!

654
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:16,156
We have plenty of time to spare.

655
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,033
Would you like a drink?

656
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:19,451
[gasps]

657
00:35:19,534 --> 00:35:22,245
[Jucheon] <i>Since things are awkward,</i>

658
00:35:22,329 --> 00:35:25,206
<i>they naturally gravitate towards</i>
<i>sharing a drink together.</i>

659
00:35:27,292 --> 00:35:29,419
[loudly gulping]

660
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:33,381
[both sigh]

661
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,092
[Jucheon] <i>One glass</i>

662
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:37,469
- <i>turns into two…</i>
- [Hari] Cheers.

663
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:40,055
[Jucheon]
<i>Their glasses keep touching until…</i>

664
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:44,893
Dr. Chiyeon, I seem to be getting drunk.

665
00:35:46,353 --> 00:35:47,437
Gosh.

666
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:53,151
I'm already drunk on your scent, Ms. Hari.

667
00:35:53,234 --> 00:35:56,738
[Jucheon] <i>Something else starts touching!</i>

668
00:35:57,405 --> 00:35:58,657
[Jeongseon] <i>Something else?</i>

669
00:35:59,449 --> 00:36:00,784
[Hari gasps]

670
00:36:03,495 --> 00:36:05,872
- [Hyeon hums]
- [Hari sighs]

671
00:36:09,959 --> 00:36:11,920
Stop!

672
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:13,880
[Jucheon] What do you think?

673
00:36:13,963 --> 00:36:15,048
Not bad, huh?

674
00:36:16,091 --> 00:36:18,218
I'm gonna go to my room now.

675
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:19,636
[Jeongseon] Okay.

676
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:22,263
[Jucheon] You're going?
Things were just getting spicy.

677
00:36:22,347 --> 00:36:26,726
[Ms. Hwang] Dr. Yong, you really put
too much thought into saying

678
00:36:26,810 --> 00:36:29,521
a whole lot you really don't need to say.

679
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:30,730
[Jiui] My point exactly!

680
00:36:30,814 --> 00:36:33,316
[Jucheon] I thought
it was super fun, though.

681
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:44,244
[innkeeper] What to do?

682
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:46,538
I'm sorry, but we only have one room left.

683
00:36:47,163 --> 00:36:48,289
Uh…

684
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:52,627
In that case…

685
00:36:52,711 --> 00:36:55,714
If it's all right with you,
would you like to stay in my room?

686
00:36:55,797 --> 00:36:57,674
Oh, no. That's fine.

687
00:36:57,757 --> 00:37:00,301
We're just grateful
that you're looking out for us.

688
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:04,222
That there's my room,
so tell me if you need anything.

689
00:37:04,305 --> 00:37:05,306
- Okay.
- Okay.

690
00:37:17,527 --> 00:37:19,237
We have plenty of time to spare.

691
00:37:20,321 --> 00:37:21,322
Would you like a drink?

692
00:37:28,705 --> 00:37:30,999
[boat engine running]

693
00:37:35,879 --> 00:37:38,298
They go around just fine,
even late at night.

694
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:45,597
[Hari] Cheers.

695
00:37:50,393 --> 00:37:52,562
- [Hyeon sighs]
- Wow!

696
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:58,151
Do you still not remember
the day we first met?

697
00:37:58,234 --> 00:37:59,694
[Hari groans]

698
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,321
Sorry.

699
00:38:02,906 --> 00:38:04,824
Well, that's disappointing.

700
00:38:05,575 --> 00:38:08,077
It was the first time in my life
I've ever been rejected.

701
00:38:09,329 --> 00:38:10,538
What?

702
00:38:10,622 --> 00:38:11,873
You rejected me,

703
00:38:12,707 --> 00:38:14,250
when I didn't even ask you out.

704
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:17,545
- What do you mean by…
- [motorcycle approaching]

705
00:38:17,629 --> 00:38:19,547
[motorcycle crashes]

706
00:38:19,631 --> 00:38:20,799
[body thuds]

707
00:38:23,092 --> 00:38:24,177
[bystander] Hello? Emergency line?

708
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:26,971
I'm the one who just called
about the motorcycle accident.

709
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:29,182
Check where they are!

710
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:30,809
[bystander] Can you tell me where you are?

711
00:38:30,892 --> 00:38:32,519
Yes. She's administering CPR.

712
00:38:32,602 --> 00:38:35,021
I'm an intern at Yeonhui University.
I'll take over.

713
00:38:35,104 --> 00:38:36,773
- Okay.
- [bystander] They're almost here!

714
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:39,108
[Hari] EMS is on the way.

715
00:38:47,534 --> 00:38:49,035
The patient's breathing again.

716
00:38:50,995 --> 00:38:52,997
EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE TEAM

717
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:01,047
Good job.

718
00:39:02,715 --> 00:39:03,716
You too.

719
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,098
Wait.

720
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,526
I'm sorry.

721
00:39:22,026 --> 00:39:24,028
- What?
- I have a boyfriend.

722
00:39:25,196 --> 00:39:27,949
- Hey, wait--
- I told you I have a boyfriend.

723
00:39:29,242 --> 00:39:30,410
That's great.

724
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:32,954
I'm sure your boyfriend
will want to reach you,

725
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:34,497
- so take this with you.
- What?

726
00:39:38,835 --> 00:39:40,211
This is yours.

727
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:45,717
Oh, my.

728
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,510
I see. How did it…

729
00:39:47,594 --> 00:39:50,972
You don't seem like
love-at-first-sight material.

730
00:39:51,723 --> 00:39:53,016
What?

731
00:39:53,099 --> 00:39:55,184
Look in the mirror.
You'll see what I mean.

732
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:56,394
Move aside.

733
00:40:01,274 --> 00:40:02,483
What's wrong with my face?

734
00:40:10,074 --> 00:40:11,075
[chuckles]

735
00:40:12,118 --> 00:40:13,286
[chuckles]

736
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:15,830
[Hari gasps]

737
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:17,165
You're the guy from…

738
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:18,958
- [chuckles]
- [Hari gasps loudly]

739
00:40:19,042 --> 00:40:20,251
Right?

740
00:40:21,085 --> 00:40:22,629
Wow. [laughs]

741
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:26,591
I'm really not usually like that.

742
00:40:26,674 --> 00:40:29,761
I was just so out of it and that was just…

743
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:32,472
- Pretty sure you're still the same.
- I'm not!

744
00:40:33,306 --> 00:40:34,432
[Hyeon chuckles]

745
00:40:42,398 --> 00:40:44,317
It's meant to be handled with care.

746
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,903
It should be handled with care.

747
00:40:48,696 --> 00:40:50,615
And we wouldn't want
anyone stealing it, so…

748
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:56,704
I'll just put it over there.

749
00:40:56,788 --> 00:40:59,707
[Mija] Hi, Hari.
How are things over there?

750
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:01,709
Do you have a place to stay?

751
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:04,420
Goodness. Don't worry about me.

752
00:41:04,504 --> 00:41:06,547
I'll take care of myself.

753
00:41:06,631 --> 00:41:09,717
Okay, I'm hanging up now.

754
00:41:12,679 --> 00:41:13,763
[grunts]

755
00:41:14,555 --> 00:41:16,641
- [Mija] Burglar!
- Wait!

756
00:41:16,724 --> 00:41:18,977
[Jiui yelling]

757
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:21,771
Who are you?

758
00:41:21,854 --> 00:41:24,565
Wait! It's me.

759
00:41:28,403 --> 00:41:30,029
[Mija] Oh, my.

760
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:32,865
- You're the doctor.
- Yes.

761
00:41:32,949 --> 00:41:34,909
What brings you here?

762
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:38,413
This. A delivery.

763
00:41:39,998 --> 00:41:41,082
Delivery…

764
00:41:41,874 --> 00:41:43,376
Oh, goodness.

765
00:41:44,377 --> 00:41:45,712
I'm sorry, ma'am.

766
00:41:48,423 --> 00:41:50,633
[Mija] Come in.

767
00:41:52,677 --> 00:41:55,346
Sit here for a bit.

768
00:41:55,430 --> 00:41:56,931
I'll bring the medicine.

769
00:42:11,571 --> 00:42:12,572
Here.

770
00:42:13,239 --> 00:42:14,240
Goodness.

771
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:16,659
Let me see.

772
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:28,379
Goodness. That's got to hurt.

773
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,007
[Jiui groans]

774
00:42:31,883 --> 00:42:32,967
[Mija laughs]

775
00:42:44,645 --> 00:42:47,065
ONE PAINKILLER
WHEN PAIN BECOMES UNBEARABLE

776
00:42:47,148 --> 00:42:49,108
TALENOL
DON'T TAKE MORE THAN FIVE

777
00:42:50,359 --> 00:42:54,697
But what kind of pain
is making you take so many…

778
00:42:56,991 --> 00:42:59,368
I didn't even get to ask you back then.

779
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:01,287
[Mija] Well…

780
00:43:01,370 --> 00:43:04,123
It's nothing.

781
00:43:04,207 --> 00:43:05,833
It's just migraines.

782
00:43:06,918 --> 00:43:08,920
It seems to be causing a lot of distress,

783
00:43:09,003 --> 00:43:12,256
but you shouldn't just take painkillers
because you're in pain.

784
00:43:12,340 --> 00:43:14,217
Don't you worry now.

785
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:15,676
I know my body--

786
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:17,011
Better than anyone else.

787
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:23,476
But even if you may think
you know your body best,

788
00:43:23,559 --> 00:43:24,977
you could be wrong.

789
00:43:25,937 --> 00:43:27,772
[♪ sincere music playing]

790
00:43:29,190 --> 00:43:30,942
Unlock your phone for me, please.

791
00:43:31,484 --> 00:43:32,693
What for?

792
00:43:40,368 --> 00:43:45,248
PH DOC DO JIUI

793
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:46,415
SAVE

794
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:49,168
This is my number.

795
00:43:49,252 --> 00:43:52,547
Give me a call
if you can't make it over to the center.

796
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:53,881
Goodness me.

797
00:43:54,966 --> 00:43:56,300
Thank you.

798
00:43:58,761 --> 00:44:00,096
[Hari] I'll sleep on this side.

799
00:44:00,179 --> 00:44:01,806
You sleep on that side.

800
00:44:02,431 --> 00:44:04,559
Are we really going to sleep
in the same room?

801
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:06,352
Yeah, it's fine.

802
00:44:06,435 --> 00:44:09,730
There are bugs outside.
How can I ask you to sleep outside?

803
00:44:09,814 --> 00:44:11,649
Let's just make do.

804
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:14,026
I didn't say
I'd be the one sleeping outside.

805
00:44:16,988 --> 00:44:17,989
What?

806
00:44:20,950 --> 00:44:22,160
I mean…

807
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:23,578
[laughs]

808
00:44:31,627 --> 00:44:33,045
[Hari] What is that?

809
00:44:35,548 --> 00:44:37,633
Did you draw a line in case I cross it?

810
00:44:39,552 --> 00:44:42,722
Wow. What do you take me for?

811
00:44:43,431 --> 00:44:45,141
I should ask the same of you, okay?

812
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:48,603
Don't you dare.
I'm going to be really mad if you do.

813
00:44:58,029 --> 00:44:59,280
[chuckles]

814
00:45:05,369 --> 00:45:07,371
[♪ amusing music playing]

815
00:45:21,093 --> 00:45:22,511
[sighs]

816
00:45:25,056 --> 00:45:26,265
[Hari snores]

817
00:45:27,558 --> 00:45:29,310
- [Hyoen chuckles]
- [snoring continues]

818
00:45:38,361 --> 00:45:42,531
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

819
00:45:46,911 --> 00:45:48,371
Good morning, everyone.

820
00:45:48,454 --> 00:45:49,872
Good morning.

821
00:45:51,207 --> 00:45:52,583
Are they back yet?

822
00:45:53,167 --> 00:45:56,337
Dr. Chiyeon's back.
I guess you didn't run into him.

823
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:57,421
No, I didn't.

824
00:46:00,216 --> 00:46:02,134
What about Ms. Hari?

825
00:46:02,218 --> 00:46:05,304
She took the day off for something.
Do you need something from her?

826
00:46:05,388 --> 00:46:07,390
No, it's nothing.

827
00:46:07,974 --> 00:46:09,308
[phone ringing]

828
00:46:12,853 --> 00:46:15,648
This is PH doc Do Jiui
at the Public Health Center.

829
00:46:15,731 --> 00:46:17,942
<i>Hey, I'm Ko Changmok.</i>

830
00:46:18,025 --> 00:46:19,402
Excuse me?

831
00:46:19,485 --> 00:46:21,237
<i>I said I'm Ko Changmok.</i>

832
00:46:21,320 --> 00:46:24,490
<i>Are you having any issues there?</i>

833
00:46:24,573 --> 00:46:25,574
Sorry?

834
00:46:25,658 --> 00:46:30,204
<i>I'm just calling to see</i>
<i>if you're having any issues over there.</i>

835
00:46:30,288 --> 00:46:31,289
Who's calling?

836
00:46:31,872 --> 00:46:33,874
Someone's asking if we have any issues.

837
00:46:33,958 --> 00:46:37,169
I'm up to my neck in work!
I don't have time to deal with that crap!

838
00:46:37,253 --> 00:46:38,963
Tell them to stop fooling around!

839
00:46:39,046 --> 00:46:41,424
<i>I'm just asking if you have any issues.</i>

840
00:46:41,507 --> 00:46:44,802
We're a little busy right now,
so would you mind visiting the center?

841
00:46:44,885 --> 00:46:46,929
- <i>Hello? He--</i>
- Thank you.

842
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:56,522
[laughs]

843
00:46:56,605 --> 00:46:58,607
Goodness me,

844
00:46:58,691 --> 00:47:03,404
our Public Health Center
seems to be busy as hell.

845
00:47:03,487 --> 00:47:06,032
This is how things are between me
and our subordinates.

846
00:47:06,115 --> 00:47:09,994
We've done away with all formalities.
We're comfortable with each other.

847
00:47:10,077 --> 00:47:11,078
YEOPOONG-GUN

848
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:12,788
[laughs]

849
00:47:15,333 --> 00:47:19,045
[narrator] <i>A helicopter cuts its way</i>
<i>across high waves and islands.</i>

850
00:47:19,712 --> 00:47:24,342
<i>Wherever the patients may be,</i>
<i>a helicopter is dispatched, on the double.</i>

851
00:47:24,925 --> 00:47:27,595
<i>A mere 10 minutes</i>
<i>after a patient is reported,</i>

852
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:30,806
<i>the helicopter</i>
<i>begins transporting the patient</i>

853
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:33,434
<i>in a stunning display</i>

854
00:47:33,517 --> 00:47:38,397
<i>of Governor Ko Changmok's</i>
<i>health care modernization initiative.</i>

855
00:47:38,481 --> 00:47:40,649
[chuckling]

856
00:47:41,734 --> 00:47:43,861
Now, as much as it pains me
to remember it,

857
00:47:43,944 --> 00:47:46,572
the image of my grandmother
grabbing my wrist

858
00:47:46,655 --> 00:47:49,700
and telling me that
one had no choice but to die

859
00:47:49,784 --> 00:47:52,870
if one were to fall sick on an island
is still seared into my heart.

860
00:47:52,953 --> 00:47:57,500
I promised to modernize health care
in Yeopoong-gun during my term of office,

861
00:47:57,583 --> 00:48:00,961
so I, Ko Changmok,
will do whatever it takes

862
00:48:01,045 --> 00:48:04,715
to overhaul our helipads

863
00:48:04,799 --> 00:48:07,259
so my grandmother's words

864
00:48:07,343 --> 00:48:11,222
don't apply to Yeopoong-gun, everyone!

865
00:48:14,725 --> 00:48:16,310
- Hey, Mr. Choi.
- Yes, sir.

866
00:48:16,394 --> 00:48:18,270
That place we called just now.

867
00:48:18,354 --> 00:48:21,774
Are you sure they recently used
a chopper to transport a patient?

868
00:48:21,857 --> 00:48:22,858
I'm sure of it, sir.

869
00:48:22,942 --> 00:48:25,653
Well, then that's no way
to respond to a call.

870
00:48:25,736 --> 00:48:27,113
I mean, Director,

871
00:48:27,196 --> 00:48:29,573
you said you strengthened
the emergency protocols.

872
00:48:29,657 --> 00:48:32,243
- Did you not finish what you started?
- I'm sorry, sir.

873
00:48:32,326 --> 00:48:33,744
Sorry just won't cut it, okay?

874
00:48:33,828 --> 00:48:37,248
Be sure to punish them
to uphold discipline.

875
00:48:37,331 --> 00:48:39,250
Yes, sir. I'll have a word with them.

876
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:42,795
Just to be clear,
I told you to punish them.

877
00:48:49,218 --> 00:48:50,386
[sighs]

878
00:49:04,316 --> 00:49:05,943
Perhaps you've fallen ill.

879
00:49:06,485 --> 00:49:08,154
[patient] Of course I've fallen ill.

880
00:49:08,237 --> 00:49:11,532
I'm coughing nonstop, like I told you.

881
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:14,660
Not even the medicine
my daughter-in-law got me is working.

882
00:49:14,743 --> 00:49:17,496
- Right.
- [patient coughing]

883
00:49:17,580 --> 00:49:22,626
I'm going to have to switch
to a stronger medicine.

884
00:49:22,710 --> 00:49:25,337
No matter how much I take my current ones,

885
00:49:25,421 --> 00:49:27,339
it doesn't seem to make a difference.

886
00:49:27,423 --> 00:49:29,758
As I said before,
there's a variety of things

887
00:49:29,842 --> 00:49:32,428
- that could be causing your cough…
- For crying out loud.

888
00:49:32,511 --> 00:49:35,014
I told you I know all about that. [coughs]

889
00:49:35,097 --> 00:49:39,768
Just get off my case
and give me stronger cough medicine.

890
00:49:39,852 --> 00:49:41,479
[coughing]

891
00:49:42,730 --> 00:49:46,192
I'll be taking that as a yes
and leaving now.

892
00:49:46,275 --> 00:49:49,195
[continues coughing]

893
00:49:54,325 --> 00:49:56,785
REVOPANSA PILL
DAYS: 30

894
00:49:56,869 --> 00:49:58,913
Morning and evening,
30 minutes after meals.

895
00:49:58,996 --> 00:50:00,748
- You know the drill, right?
- Yes.

896
00:50:01,749 --> 00:50:04,001
I switched to a stronger medicine.

897
00:50:09,048 --> 00:50:10,508
Ms. Hwang.

898
00:50:10,591 --> 00:50:12,801
I'm sorry,
I received the ID photo too late.

899
00:50:12,885 --> 00:50:14,845
You certainly took your sweet time.

900
00:50:14,929 --> 00:50:17,389
I see Mr. Jangsu's switching his meds.

901
00:50:17,473 --> 00:50:20,601
- He said he needed something stronger.
- Is he a doctor or something?

902
00:50:20,684 --> 00:50:22,728
Who's he to tell us
to give him stronger meds?

903
00:50:22,811 --> 00:50:25,022
[sighs] That's how it is
with everyone here.

904
00:50:25,105 --> 00:50:26,690
They all know their own body best.

905
00:50:26,774 --> 00:50:28,484
If he knew his body so well,

906
00:50:28,567 --> 00:50:31,654
how did he end up getting a heart attack
and needing a stent?

907
00:50:31,737 --> 00:50:33,072
What a load of rubbish.

908
00:50:33,614 --> 00:50:34,823
A heart…

909
00:50:35,950 --> 00:50:37,201
Heart attack?

910
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,119
[Ms. Hwang] <i>Didn't he tell you?</i>

911
00:50:39,203 --> 00:50:42,998
<i>Mr. Jangsu also got a stent inserted</i>
<i>last year, just like Mr. Park.</i>

912
00:50:43,082 --> 00:50:45,543
I never heard anything of the sort.

913
00:50:45,626 --> 00:50:47,294
That wasn't in his medical records.

914
00:50:47,378 --> 00:50:48,462
Scoot over.

915
00:50:48,546 --> 00:50:50,798
"Stent insertion, myocardial infarction."

916
00:50:51,632 --> 00:50:53,175
MEDICAL RECORD NOT FOUND

917
00:50:53,259 --> 00:50:55,678
It's not here!

918
00:50:55,761 --> 00:50:58,347
- <i>I guess it hasn't been updated yet.</i>
- [Jiui] <i>Oh, no!</i>

919
00:50:58,430 --> 00:51:02,226
<i>Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs</i>
<i>can cause side effects or death</i>

920
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:04,979
<i>for patients with a history</i>
<i>of myocardial infarction.</i>

921
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:07,231
Is he seriously trying to ruin my life?

922
00:51:07,314 --> 00:51:12,695
[on radio] <i>Jangsu's Herbal Medicine.</i>
<i>Let it energize…</i>

923
00:51:12,778 --> 00:51:13,988
Mr. Lee Jangsu!

924
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:15,698
Are you kidding me right now?

925
00:51:15,781 --> 00:51:20,536
[on radio] <i>Black garlic extract</i>
<i>that's damn good for chronic fatigue,</i>

926
00:51:20,619 --> 00:51:24,707
<i>also great for hangovers,</i>
<i>detoxing your liver, and…</i>

927
00:51:24,790 --> 00:51:26,875
Hey, Mr. Lee Jangsu!

928
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:28,752
Mr. Lee Jangsu!

929
00:51:29,545 --> 00:51:32,673
[♪ upbeat music playing on speakers]

930
00:51:32,756 --> 00:51:33,966
Hey…

931
00:51:34,049 --> 00:51:35,843
Hey, Mr. Lee Jangsu!

932
00:51:37,886 --> 00:51:39,305
Mr. Lee Jangsu!

933
00:51:39,388 --> 00:51:41,015
♪ <i>Twirl round and round</i> ♪

934
00:51:41,098 --> 00:51:42,099
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

935
00:51:42,182 --> 00:51:43,684
♪ <i>Till the night is over</i> ♪

936
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:45,436
♪ <i>Twirl round and round</i> ♪

937
00:51:45,519 --> 00:51:46,729
- Mr. Lee!
- ♪ <i>Through the night</i> ♪

938
00:51:46,812 --> 00:51:49,481
♪ <i>And until the day goes by</i> ♪

939
00:51:49,565 --> 00:51:51,233
Hey, Lee Jangsu!

940
00:51:53,527 --> 00:51:55,362
Hey, Lee Jangsu!

941
00:51:55,446 --> 00:51:56,447
Goddamn it!

942
00:51:58,532 --> 00:51:59,783
Mr. Lee Jangsu!

943
00:52:03,829 --> 00:52:04,830
I'm back!

944
00:52:07,583 --> 00:52:08,834
Damn.

945
00:52:08,917 --> 00:52:11,754
JANGSU'S HERBAL MEDICINE

946
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:13,672
You're back?

947
00:52:20,512 --> 00:52:21,513
Seriously.

948
00:52:24,350 --> 00:52:25,517
Lee Jangsu!

949
00:52:30,648 --> 00:52:32,900
What the… Dr. Do?

950
00:52:36,737 --> 00:52:40,199
Mr. Lee, did you have
a heart attack before?

951
00:52:41,367 --> 00:52:42,618
Yes. So what?

952
00:52:42,701 --> 00:52:44,286
Why didn't you tell me that?

953
00:52:45,412 --> 00:52:48,290
I mean, it's not like telling you
would have done any good.

954
00:52:48,374 --> 00:52:50,501
It's not like
you're going to cure my heart!

955
00:52:50,584 --> 00:52:54,338
For someone with a history
of myocardial infarction, NSAIDs…

956
00:52:54,421 --> 00:52:56,215
[Jiui breathes shakily]

957
00:52:58,050 --> 00:52:59,051
The thing is…

958
00:52:59,134 --> 00:53:01,637
you could suffer side effects
if you take those drugs.

959
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:04,682
It could even kill you,
so give me the meds right now!

960
00:53:07,518 --> 00:53:10,187
The meds you're taking right now.
Hand those over as well.

961
00:53:10,270 --> 00:53:12,981
The ones my daughter-in-law got for me?

962
00:53:13,065 --> 00:53:14,942
Yes, I need to know what they are.

963
00:53:15,025 --> 00:53:18,195
I'll go get them. Give me a second.

964
00:53:18,278 --> 00:53:20,531
And I prescribed all this
without knowing that!

965
00:53:23,158 --> 00:53:25,411
[panting]

966
00:53:27,788 --> 00:53:29,998
MAPRYL

967
00:53:31,166 --> 00:53:33,085
<i>An ACE inhibitor.</i>

968
00:53:33,627 --> 00:53:36,839
<i>Just as I thought, the coughs</i>
<i>were a side effect of his meds.</i>

969
00:53:37,965 --> 00:53:40,134
The reason you've been coughing,

970
00:53:40,217 --> 00:53:42,886
it's probably a side effect of these meds.

971
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:44,388
You have to switch right now.

972
00:53:44,471 --> 00:53:47,266
Get a new prescription
from the hospital that did your stent.

973
00:53:47,349 --> 00:53:48,475
Okay.

974
00:53:59,153 --> 00:54:00,279
This is why…

975
00:54:04,324 --> 00:54:09,705
This is why patients have to be
forthcoming about their medical history.

976
00:54:09,788 --> 00:54:13,834
Even if you think you know your body well,
you need to consult your doctor first.

977
00:54:13,917 --> 00:54:15,878
That's what doctors are for!
Do you understand?

978
00:54:18,172 --> 00:54:19,590
I understand.

979
00:54:21,717 --> 00:54:22,718
I'm going now.

980
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:28,390
Hey, Doctor!

981
00:54:30,392 --> 00:54:31,477
What is it now?

982
00:54:35,147 --> 00:54:36,940
Thank you.

983
00:54:37,024 --> 00:54:39,693
Goodness me. Thank you.

984
00:54:41,403 --> 00:54:47,409
I mean, you came running all this way
just to save my life, didn't you?

985
00:54:47,493 --> 00:54:49,912
Not even my son or my daughter-in-law

986
00:54:49,995 --> 00:54:51,955
would have gone to such lengths
to help me.

987
00:54:52,748 --> 00:54:54,541
[wife] You're absolutely right.

988
00:54:54,625 --> 00:54:56,877
Thank you so much.

989
00:54:56,960 --> 00:55:02,341
I won't touch those pills
for the rest of my life,

990
00:55:02,424 --> 00:55:05,385
- so don't worry about me, okay?
- Right.

991
00:55:10,557 --> 00:55:11,558
Okay.

992
00:55:17,856 --> 00:55:18,857
[wife] Take care.

993
00:55:20,817 --> 00:55:21,818
Goodness.

994
00:55:23,487 --> 00:55:25,781
[Jangsu] Maybe I should've
given him some melons.

995
00:55:25,864 --> 00:55:27,449
[wife] Gosh, you're right.

996
00:55:48,428 --> 00:55:49,638
Hey, Doctor.

997
00:55:50,889 --> 00:55:52,099
Hello there.

998
00:55:53,058 --> 00:55:58,063
I did exactly what you told me to
and did some exercise,

999
00:55:58,146 --> 00:56:00,148
and my tongue's all healed now.

1000
00:56:00,983 --> 00:56:04,861
I should invite you over
for a meal sometime.

1001
00:56:06,697 --> 00:56:07,906
I see.

1002
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:10,659
Now then, you should be on your way.

1003
00:56:31,388 --> 00:56:32,389
CLOSED FOR THE DAY

1004
00:56:32,472 --> 00:56:35,225
VISITING A MAINLAND HOSPITAL
DUE TO A HAND INJURY

1005
00:56:35,309 --> 00:56:37,728
CLIFFSIDE RAW FISH RESTAURANT

1006
00:56:55,954 --> 00:56:57,331
Gosh.

1007
00:56:57,414 --> 00:56:59,916
Dr. Do, are you okay?

1008
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:02,544
I'll prescribe a different medicine
for Mr. Lee.

1009
00:57:02,628 --> 00:57:03,754
[Ms. Hwang] Right.

1010
00:57:04,671 --> 00:57:07,174
Goodness me.
Mr. Park, what brings you here?

1011
00:57:12,679 --> 00:57:14,306
[Mr. Park] Have some of this.

1012
00:57:15,432 --> 00:57:17,267
Oh, my!

1013
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:18,935
- Goodness!
- Sorry?

1014
00:57:20,395 --> 00:57:22,147
Goodness gracious!

1015
00:57:22,230 --> 00:57:23,649
Or toss it if you don't want it.

1016
00:57:23,732 --> 00:57:24,941
Dr. Do.

1017
00:57:28,070 --> 00:57:30,113
What's going on?

1018
00:57:31,031 --> 00:57:33,492
I went to the hospital to look into it.

1019
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:35,994
Turns out the insurance company
tried to cheat him.

1020
00:57:36,078 --> 00:57:38,080
[♪ emotional music playing]

1021
00:57:38,163 --> 00:57:40,957
They rejected the claim
for Mr. Park's stent procedure

1022
00:57:41,041 --> 00:57:44,544
for myocardial infarction,
classifying it as angina instead.

1023
00:57:45,754 --> 00:57:47,923
And I just took their word for it.

1024
00:57:49,508 --> 00:57:51,677
They argued that
it wasn't myocardial infarction

1025
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:53,887
because there was no ST segment elevation,

1026
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:55,555
but his report clearly states

1027
00:57:55,639 --> 00:57:58,266
that it was a non-ST-segment elevation
myocardial infarction,

1028
00:57:58,350 --> 00:58:00,143
so it was indeed a myocardial infarction.

1029
00:58:00,227 --> 00:58:02,145
That means you can claim your payout.

1030
00:58:02,229 --> 00:58:03,230
Right.

1031
00:58:03,313 --> 00:58:04,439
It may take a while,

1032
00:58:04,523 --> 00:58:07,484
but you can still get your payout
if you file for compensation

1033
00:58:07,567 --> 00:58:10,445
with the Korea Consumer Agency
and make an insurance claim.

1034
00:58:10,529 --> 00:58:13,699
Wow, so you went there in person
to look into everything?

1035
00:58:14,282 --> 00:58:17,119
- Yeah.
- Goodness me, you precious thing.

1036
00:58:17,202 --> 00:58:20,455
You really were trained
at a big university hospital.

1037
00:58:20,539 --> 00:58:24,209
How are you so smart?
This is such great news.

1038
00:58:24,292 --> 00:58:25,502
I should get going now.

1039
00:58:25,585 --> 00:58:28,714
Okay, we won't walk you out.

1040
00:58:29,631 --> 00:58:30,924
And…

1041
00:58:31,007 --> 00:58:34,261
my wife will be bringing lunch
for the center tomorrow.

1042
00:58:36,012 --> 00:58:37,556
I told her to bring meat dishes.

1043
00:58:37,639 --> 00:58:38,640
Okay.

1044
00:58:39,725 --> 00:58:40,934
Dr. Do Jiui…

1045
00:58:43,645 --> 00:58:45,313
enjoy the food, okay?

1046
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:48,692
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

1047
00:58:50,277 --> 00:58:53,029
- You precious thing.
- [Hari] I did good, didn't I?

1048
00:58:54,614 --> 00:58:55,615
Let me prepare those.

1049
00:58:55,699 --> 00:58:57,826
Sure. Just how many are there?

1050
00:58:57,909 --> 00:58:59,619
We're gonna have ourselves a feast.

1051
00:59:13,633 --> 00:59:14,676
[sighs]

1052
00:59:14,760 --> 00:59:18,263
I'LL BE OUT FOR A WHILE
I'LL LEAVE IT UP TO YOUR CONSCIENCE

1053
00:59:26,271 --> 00:59:27,856
[door opening]

1054
00:59:35,113 --> 00:59:36,656
Were you waiting for me?

1055
00:59:37,449 --> 00:59:38,533
Me, wait for you?

1056
00:59:38,617 --> 00:59:41,578
Not at all. I was just…

1057
00:59:42,996 --> 00:59:45,373
[Hari] You look like
you've got something to say.

1058
00:59:48,210 --> 00:59:49,419
If not, never mind.

1059
00:59:49,503 --> 00:59:50,921
[stammering] Thank you.

1060
00:59:52,172 --> 00:59:53,465
[scoffs]

1061
00:59:53,548 --> 00:59:55,550
Was that so hard?

1062
00:59:58,970 --> 01:00:00,806
Care to join me for some beer?

1063
01:00:06,228 --> 01:00:07,229
Cheers.

1064
01:00:13,944 --> 01:00:16,238
There's something I want to ask you.

1065
01:00:16,863 --> 01:00:17,864
[Jiui] Mmm.

1066
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:21,618
Why did you send this to me?

1067
01:00:23,161 --> 01:00:25,539
I actually sent that by accident.

1068
01:00:25,622 --> 01:00:28,875
[Hari] I had a good laugh.
Isn't it hilarious?

1069
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:30,627
Delete it.

1070
01:00:30,710 --> 01:00:33,129
[Hari] No. I'm going to look at it
whenever I feel down.

1071
01:00:41,680 --> 01:00:44,224
You should also take a look
and get a laugh out of it.

1072
01:00:46,393 --> 01:00:47,477
Okay?

1073
01:00:47,561 --> 01:00:48,562
Okay.

1074
01:00:50,438 --> 01:00:53,233
You've had a dark cloud
hanging over your head all day.

1075
01:00:57,696 --> 01:00:59,155
Did something happen?

1076
01:01:02,701 --> 01:01:04,411
Well…

1077
01:01:08,498 --> 01:01:10,792
I prescribed an NSAID to a patient

1078
01:01:12,127 --> 01:01:14,671
with a history
of myocardial infarction today.

1079
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:15,755
What?

1080
01:01:16,256 --> 01:01:18,675
Do they know they shouldn't take it?

1081
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:22,929
That's why I ran after him
to tell him not to take it.

1082
01:01:23,013 --> 01:01:24,431
I see.

1083
01:01:25,015 --> 01:01:27,017
Because taking it might have killed him.

1084
01:01:30,979 --> 01:01:32,188
But here's the thing…

1085
01:01:34,065 --> 01:01:37,110
I wasn't worried about the patient
as I was chasing after him.

1086
01:01:38,820 --> 01:01:40,238
I only worried about myself.

1087
01:01:42,657 --> 01:01:45,327
If someone were to find out
I prescribed the wrong meds,

1088
01:01:45,410 --> 01:01:48,914
they could have filed a complaint,
which would lead to disciplinary action

1089
01:01:48,997 --> 01:01:52,000
and me getting trapped on this island.

1090
01:01:53,668 --> 01:01:55,754
[♪ emotional music playing]

1091
01:01:55,837 --> 01:01:57,881
<i>I ran after him to save myself.</i>

1092
01:02:01,968 --> 01:02:02,969
But…

1093
01:02:06,598 --> 01:02:08,600
the patient thanked me.

1094
01:02:11,144 --> 01:02:12,729
For saving his life.

1095
01:02:16,816 --> 01:02:20,111
I lashed out so many times
because people looked down on PH docs…

1096
01:02:22,489 --> 01:02:24,115
but it turns out I was the one…

1097
01:02:26,785 --> 01:02:28,244
who looked down on myself most.

1098
01:02:30,038 --> 01:02:31,247
Despite being a doctor…

1099
01:02:33,333 --> 01:02:35,543
I decided to do nothing.

1100
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:45,720
Doctor…

1101
01:02:46,846 --> 01:02:48,431
come with me.

1102
01:02:49,265 --> 01:02:50,266
What?

1103
01:02:51,226 --> 01:02:53,728
- Come on.
- What? Where…

1104
01:02:54,270 --> 01:02:55,772
You'll see when we get there.

1105
01:03:00,026 --> 01:03:02,070
[Jiui] What on earth are you looking for?

1106
01:03:02,153 --> 01:03:04,823
[Hari] Just give it a second.

1107
01:03:04,906 --> 01:03:06,908
There's something I want to show you.

1108
01:03:07,534 --> 01:03:09,494
[Jiui] I get that, but what is it?

1109
01:03:09,577 --> 01:03:13,123
It's not something
you can come across that easily, but…

1110
01:03:15,333 --> 01:03:16,793
That's odd.

1111
01:03:19,504 --> 01:03:22,716
They should be showing up right about now.

1112
01:03:27,303 --> 01:03:29,305
I'm going to climb my way down now.

1113
01:03:32,559 --> 01:03:34,102
[gasps] Wait!

1114
01:03:35,437 --> 01:03:36,813
Come here!

1115
01:03:37,856 --> 01:03:39,649
What is it?

1116
01:03:39,733 --> 01:03:40,817
[Hari] Be quiet.

1117
01:03:57,959 --> 01:03:59,085
[gasps]

1118
01:04:01,629 --> 01:04:02,714
[Hari giggles]

1119
01:04:02,797 --> 01:04:04,632
[♪ gentle melodic music playing]

1120
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:09,846
[Jiui] I've never seen fireflies before.

1121
01:04:09,929 --> 01:04:11,139
[Hari] Really?

1122
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:13,850
- [Jiui] Wow.
- [Hari laughs]

1123
01:04:16,895 --> 01:04:18,104
What do you think?

1124
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,065
Aren't they beautiful?

1125
01:04:23,735 --> 01:04:25,570
What did I tell you?

1126
01:04:25,653 --> 01:04:27,655
I told you they'd show up soon.

1127
01:04:31,826 --> 01:04:32,994
They're beautiful, right?

1128
01:04:46,174 --> 01:04:47,509
By the way, Dr. Do…

1129
01:04:50,887 --> 01:04:52,222
this island

1130
01:04:53,515 --> 01:04:55,725
and the people here are just as beautiful

1131
01:04:55,809 --> 01:04:58,436
when you look at them from up close.

1132
01:05:04,234 --> 01:05:08,613
I'm sorry to have to keep telling you
to bear with it all the time.

1133
01:05:10,657 --> 01:05:13,868
But you doctors are the only ones
the people here can depend on

1134
01:05:14,869 --> 01:05:16,538
when they get sick.

1135
01:05:19,249 --> 01:05:22,919
So please go easy on them. Okay?

1136
01:05:23,002 --> 01:05:24,045
[chuckles]

1137
01:05:27,215 --> 01:05:28,967
- [Jiui scoffs]
- [laughs]

1138
01:05:29,926 --> 01:05:31,094
[Jucheon grunts]

1139
01:05:35,390 --> 01:05:38,226
Dr. Chiyeon, do you want to have a beer?

1140
01:05:38,977 --> 01:05:41,396
[Hyeon] No, I'm going to sleep early.

1141
01:05:41,479 --> 01:05:43,022
I didn't get any sleep last night.

1142
01:05:43,106 --> 01:05:45,316
[♪ comical music playing]

1143
01:05:45,900 --> 01:05:49,195
[stammers] So you didn't
get any sleep on Madeokdo?

1144
01:05:49,279 --> 01:05:50,280
No.

1145
01:05:51,239 --> 01:05:52,323
Have a good rest.

1146
01:05:52,407 --> 01:05:54,868
[door opens, closes]

1147
01:05:55,368 --> 01:05:57,036
- I knew it.
- [phone pinging]

1148
01:05:59,956 --> 01:06:01,749
What's got everyone so worked up?

1149
01:06:03,459 --> 01:06:04,878
[messenger 1] <i>Stop everything. Major PSA.</i>

1150
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:07,463
<i>Has a nurse recently joined</i>
<i>any of your health centers?</i>

1151
01:06:07,547 --> 01:06:10,216
<i>Apparently, she's notorious</i>
<i>for being a doctor hunter!</i>

1152
01:06:10,300 --> 01:06:11,551
[messenger 2] <i>A doctor hunter?</i>

1153
01:06:12,135 --> 01:06:13,553
[Jucheon] Hmm?

1154
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:16,139
[messenger 3] <i>Do you mean</i>
<i>the short-haired gold digger?</i>

1155
01:06:16,222 --> 01:06:18,766
<i>The one from Asong Hospital,</i>
<i>with the mole on her nose!</i>

1156
01:06:18,850 --> 01:06:21,060
<i>I heard about her from an older colleague.</i>

1157
01:06:21,144 --> 01:06:23,479
<i>Asong Hospital's infamous nurse</i>
<i>who targets doctors!</i>

1158
01:06:27,025 --> 01:06:30,778
A nurse from Asong Hospital?

1159
01:06:30,862 --> 01:06:32,447
[Ms. Hwang]
<i>Ms. Hari here is an intellectual</i>

1160
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:36,201
<i>who used to work</i>
<i>in a university hospital's ER.</i>

1161
01:06:36,284 --> 01:06:40,330
<i>Not just any hospital,</i>
<i>but Asong Hospital…</i> [echoing]

1162
01:06:42,415 --> 01:06:43,833
Could it be…

1163
01:06:46,502 --> 01:06:47,795
Yuk Hari?

1164
01:06:54,469 --> 01:06:56,304
Can I ask you something?

1165
01:06:57,013 --> 01:06:58,139
Mmm.

1166
01:07:01,017 --> 01:07:02,268
Why did you go to Madeokdo…

1167
01:07:03,895 --> 01:07:07,232
with Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon?

1168
01:07:08,399 --> 01:07:09,400
Oh.

1169
01:07:10,193 --> 01:07:12,570
How could I have gone there with you?

1170
01:07:12,654 --> 01:07:14,197
It's not within walking distance.

1171
01:07:16,783 --> 01:07:19,077
It's over an hour away by boat.

1172
01:07:21,621 --> 01:07:22,830
Ah.

1173
01:07:26,209 --> 01:07:28,336
So you were looking out for me.

1174
01:07:29,796 --> 01:07:31,005
I didn't even realize that.

1175
01:07:34,968 --> 01:07:37,011
But I kind of regret it.

1176
01:07:41,975 --> 01:07:43,810
Maybe I shouldn't have looked out for you…

1177
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:48,273
and just gone there with you.

1178
01:07:59,117 --> 01:08:00,285
Next time…

1179
01:08:02,620 --> 01:08:04,247
do you want to go with me?

1180
01:08:06,541 --> 01:08:08,710
[♪ romantic music playing]

1181
01:08:32,150 --> 01:08:35,486
EVEN IF YOU THINK
YOU KNOW YOUR BODY WELL,

1182
01:08:35,570 --> 01:08:40,408
YOU NEED TO CONSULT
YOUR DOCTOR FIRST

1183
01:08:40,491 --> 01:08:45,705
THAT'S WHAT DOCTORS ARE FOR

1184
01:09:00,303 --> 01:09:04,223
YOU HAVE TO BE QUIET TO
SEE THE FIREFLIES

1185
01:09:12,315 --> 01:09:15,234
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

1186
01:09:16,069 --> 01:09:20,740
<i>So you're saying Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon is</i>
<i>going out with Ms. Yuk Hari, huh?</i>

1187
01:09:20,823 --> 01:09:23,159
[Geumja]
<i>You could see hearts in their eyes.</i>

1188
01:09:23,242 --> 01:09:25,745
<i>Looks like we might be having</i>
<i>a wedding on Pyeondongdo!</i>

1189
01:09:25,828 --> 01:09:27,872
It didn't seem to be just a rumor.

1190
01:09:27,955 --> 01:09:29,290
[Hyeon] <i>Does it bother you that much?</i>

1191
01:09:29,374 --> 01:09:30,875
[Jiui] <i>I had no idea</i>

1192
01:09:30,958 --> 01:09:32,460
<i>that you and Dr. Chiyeon were…</i>

1193
01:09:33,503 --> 01:09:35,838
So you were scared
that I'd get my hooks in?

1194
01:09:36,672 --> 01:09:38,549
[Jucheon] <i>I'm telling you,</i>

1195
01:09:38,633 --> 01:09:40,385
<i>she's definitely gotten her hooks in!</i>

1196
01:09:45,098 --> 01:09:47,100
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park
